parent.description: Required. The parent resource where this ``Report`` will be created. Format: ``networks/{network_code}``

name.description: Identifier. The resource name of the report. Report resource name have the form: ``networks/{network_code}/reports/{report_id}``

visibility.description: Optional. The visibility of a report.

report_definition.description: Required. The report definition of the report.

dimensions.description: Required. The list of dimensions to report on. If empty, the report will have no dimensions, and any metrics will be totals.

metrics.description: Required. The list of metrics to report on. If empty, the report will have no metrics.

name.description: Required. Metric name, e.g., "nodes total", "percent done".

int_value.description: For metrics with integer value.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``value``.

double_value.description: For metrics with floating point value.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``value``.

string_value.description: For metrics with custom values (ratios, visual progress, etc.).  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``value``.

filters.description: Optional. The filters for this report.

type_.description: Output only. The full name of the event type (for example, "google.cloud.storage.object.v1.finalized"). In the form of {provider-specific-prefix}.{resource}.{version}.{verb}. Types MUST be versioned and event schemas are guaranteed to remain backward compatible within one version. Note that event type versions and API versions do not need to match.

description.description: Output only. Human friendly description of what the event type is about. For example "Bucket created in Cloud Storage".

filtering_attributes.description: Output only. Filtering attributes for the event type.

attribute.description: Output only. Attribute used for filtering the event type.

description.description: Output only. Description of the purpose of the attribute.

required.description: Output only. If true, the triggers for this provider should always specify a filter on these attributes. Trigger creation will fail otherwise.

path_pattern_supported.description: Output only. If true, the attribute accepts matching expressions in the Eventarc PathPattern format.

event_schema_uri.description: Output only. URI for the event schema. For example "https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloudevents/blob/master/proto/google/events/cloud/storage/v1/events.proto".

time_zone.description: Optional. The time zone the date range is defined in for this report. Defaults to publisher's time zone if not specified. Time zone in IANA format. Acceptable values depend on the report type. Publisher time zone is always accepted. Use "America/Los_Angeles" for pacific time, or "Etc/UTC" for UTC.

currency_code.description: Optional. The ISO 4217 currency code for this report. Defaults to publisher currency code if not specified.

date_range.description: Required. The primary date range of this report.

fixed.description: A fixed date range.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``date_range_type``.

start_date.description: Required. The start date of this date range.

end_date.description: Required. The end date (inclusive) of this date range.

relative.description: A relative date range.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``date_range_type``.

comparison_date_range.description: Optional. The comparison date range of this report. If unspecified, the report will not have any comparison metrics.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``_comparison_date_range``.

fixed.description: A fixed date range.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``date_range_type``.

start_date.description: Required. The start date of this date range.
